                <note rend="inline" type="source">883.05/229: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Agent
                        and Consul General at Cairo</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sprigg</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-10-18T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 18, 1921—8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>20. Your 31, October 12, 6 P.M.</p>
                <p>Position of this Government regarding extension of Mixed Court arrangement
                    contingent upon action of appropriate authorities on our nominations for
                    Appellate Court. British Embassy here so informed September 20.<note n="21"
                        xml:id="d851fn21">See note of Sept 20 to the British Ambassador, <ref
                            target="#pg_915">p. 915</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
